Landon Carnie and his twin sister Lorie were initially thought to have died when the first flight of Operation Babylift crashed minutes after take-off in Vietnam on April 4, 1975 . 
  The 17-month-old twins were found huddled together in a rice paddy a day after the crash . 
  They were later taken to their adoptive parents in the U . 
 S . 
  who had been told they were dead . 
  Landon is thought to be the first child survivor to return to the crash scene . 
